 Officer of [[USS Ronald Reagan]] (CVN 76). In June of 2017, Crozier took command of the [[USS Blue Ridge (LCC-19)|USS Blue Ridge]] in Yokosuka, Japan.\n\nCrozier was the captain of the [[aircraft carrier]] [[USS Theodore Roosevelt (CVN-71)|USS ''Theodore Roosevelt'']] until he was relieved by [[United States Secretary of the Navy|US Navy Secretary]] [[Thomas Modly]], after a letter of his complaint over infections among his crew related to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] was leaked. At the time of his removal, some 114 crew members (of a total compliment of around 4,000) had been reported to be positive for the coronavirus. <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-52145230|title=US Navy removes captain who raised virus alarm|date=2020-04-03|work=BBC News|access-date=2020-04-03|language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/04/02/politics/uss-roosevelt-commander-relieved/index.html|title=Commander of aircraft carrier hit by coronavirus removed for 'poor judgment' after sounding alarm|last=CNN|first=Ryan Browne, Zachary Cohen and Jamie Crawford|website=CNN|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=Borger|first=Julian|url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2020/apr/02/us-navy-uss-theodore-roosevelt-coronavirus|title=US navy fires commander who raised alarm about coronavirus on ship|date=2020-04-02|work=The Guardian|access-date=2020-04-03|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref>\n\n== Honors, awards, and decorations ==\n{| style=\"margin-left:auto; margin-right:auto;\"\n|-\n|colspan=\"3\" |[[File:Naval Aviator Badge.jpg|220px|center]]\n|-\n|{{Ribbon devices|number=1|type=award-star|ribbon=Legion of Merit ribbon.svg|width=106}}\n|{{Ribbon devices|number=5|type=award-oak|ribbon=Defense Meritorious Service Medal ribbon.svg|width=106}}\n|{{Ribbon devices|number=0|type=award-oak|ribbon=Meritorious Service Medal ribbon.svg|width=106}}\n|-\n|{{ribbon devices|number=0|type=oak|ribbon=Air Medal ribbon.svg{{!}}border|wid